data.name: Roasted Vegetable and Chicken Bowl
data.quickTastyDescription: A hearty bowl of roasted vegetables and tender chicken, drizzled with a tangy dressing, perfect for a healthy yet satisfying meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: On a baking sheet, toss the diced bell peppers, sliced zucchini, and carrots with olive oil, garlic powder, dried oregano, salt, and pepper.
Spread the vegetables out in a single layer and roast in the oven for about 20 minutes, until they are tender and slightly caramelized.
While the vegetables are roasting, season the chicken breasts with salt, pepper, and a sprinkle of garlic powder.

In a skillet over medium heat, cook the chicken breasts for about 6-7 minutes on each side or until cooked through and juices run clear. Remove from heat and let rest for a few minutes before slicing.
In a large bowl, combine the fresh spinach, roasted vegetables, and sliced chicken. Add the halved cherry tomatoes.
Drizzle with balsamic vinegar and toss gently to combine. Serve warm or at room temperature.
